solutions.content:
# Intuition
Start from bottom.
At a node, there are 3 options:
* Choose the left path (left sum - lc)
* Choose the right path (right sum - rc)
* Choosing none (0)

The path is selected by checking the maximum value of these 3 options.
Adding the sum to node's value acts like selecting a maximum sum path.

Bends can be handled easily just by adding left value , right value and node value for the node.

The maximum of all values for all nodes is our answer.

# Approach
Store the nodes in a stack in level wise order (Bottom first and right to left)
Pop and store elements from this stack. Make a variable that stores the sum of paths that have bends in them.
Update the node's value by adding the larger of left path sum and right path sum(making sure new value is a greater value). 
The new result will be maximum of bended value, the node value and old result.

When the stack is finished, res will return the maximum path sum.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)
- Space complexity:
O(n)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxPathSum(TreeNode* root) {
        stack<TreeNode*> st;
        queue<TreeNode*> level;
        level.push(root);
        while(!level.empty()){
            TreeNode* temp = level.front();
            level.pop();
            st.push(temp);
            if(temp->left){
                level.push(temp->left);
            }
            if(temp->right){
                level.push(temp->right);
            }
        }
        int res=INT_MIN;
        while(!st.empty()){
            TreeNode* temp = st.top();
            st.pop();
            int lc = temp->left? temp->left->val : 0;
            int rc = temp->right? temp->right->val : 0;
            int bend = lc + rc + temp->val;
            temp->val += max(0,max(lc,rc));
            res = max(bend,max(res,temp->val));
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

