# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Well if you read the question carefully and observe ...you will get the vibe of easy dfs only where we need to store all possibilities at each node and store the maximum of them. 


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here we have 4 possibilities
1. ans will lie in below three only (2nd example)
2. ans will lie somewhere upper root side which take advantage of left part of current node
3. ans will lie somewhere upper root side which take advantage of right part of current node
4. ans will be just root without any previous involvement.(ex-[2,-1]...here ans will be 2 only)
At every point we return left_part_max and righ_part_max
lets take a variable to store res which takes the maximum of all 4 possibilities.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
//--------------------------------normal dfs----------------
    pair<int,int> dfs(TreeNode *root,int &res){
        if(root==NULL) return {0,0};
        pair<int,int> left_part = dfs(root->left,res);
        pair<int,int> right_part = dfs(root->right,res);
        // if your desired tree exist below this root only hemce no upper connection
        int no_upper_conn  = max(left_part.first,left_part.second)+max(right_part.first,right_part.second)+root->val;
        //if your desired tree constitute of left part only
        int max_left_part  = max(left_part.first,left_part.second)  +root->val ;
        //if your desired tree constitute of right part only
        int max_right_part = max(right_part.first,right_part.second)+root->val ;
        //RES will be max of all 4 possibilities
        res = max({res,no_upper_conn,max_left_part,max_right_part,root->val});
        //and also IT MAY CONSIST OF ONLY ROOT NODE e.g;[1,-2,3] , [2,1] 
        //that's why we check max with root->val also
        return {max(max_left_part,root->val),max(max_right_part,root->val)};
    }
    int maxPathSum(TreeNode* root) {
        int res=INT_MIN;
        dfs(root,res);
        return res;
    }
};
```

